1
00:00:11,916 --> 00:00:14,458
[typing]

2
00:00:32,375 --> 00:00:33,666
[sighs]

3
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:35,166
The reviews and comments

4
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:36,875
for episode two are horrible.

5
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,583
And I doubt
it's gonna get any better.

6
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,500
I'm completely done for.

7
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,625
Why did I even work
so hard on it?

8
00:00:49,375 --> 00:00:51,250
And you have
to supervise it all.

9
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:52,750
As soon as we're wrapped,
I'm gonna need

10
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:55,416
some serious tabletop RPG time.

11
00:00:57,125 --> 00:00:59,000
I got a job for you, Haruto.

12
00:00:59,083 --> 00:00:59,875
[HARUTO]
Huh?

13
00:00:59,958 --> 00:01:01,458
I wanna play a TRPG,

14
00:01:01,541 --> 00:01:03,875
so I need you
to be the gamemaster.

15
00:01:03,958 --> 00:01:05,666
[HARUTO]
That came out of nowhere.

16
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:08,000
I've been thinking about
trying one for a while now.

17
00:01:08,083 --> 00:01:10,458
And you seem like you have
the time on your hands.

18
00:01:10,541 --> 00:01:12,625
[Haruto] Uh, I still have
quite a bit of work

19
00:01:12,708 --> 00:01:13,750
on my plate, man.

20
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:16,041
Well, guess what?
I don't care.

21
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:18,791
[sighs]
All right.

22
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:20,041
Could be fun.

23
00:01:20,125 --> 00:01:21,583
Not like I have a choice.

24
00:01:21,666 --> 00:01:22,541
Cool.

25
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:25,458
We need more people,
so I'll text Kanikou,

26
00:01:25,541 --> 00:01:27,208
Chihiro, and Miyako.

27
00:01:28,541 --> 00:01:29,916
Sure.

28
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:30,916
Sounds good.

29
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:06,583
Um, so TRPG stands for
Tabletop Role-Playing Game?

30
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,208
I can't say I've ever heard
of that before.

31
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:11,791
I've heard of the term,
but that's about it.

32
00:03:11,875 --> 00:03:14,125
I've read a retelling
of a campaign before

33
00:03:14,208 --> 00:03:16,166
but never actually
played anything myself.

34
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:19,166
Well, a TRPG is a game
where you advance

35
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:21,500
by interacting with characters
within a world

36
00:03:21,583 --> 00:03:22,833
and roll a dice to determine

37
00:03:22,916 --> 00:03:24,833
how your decisions
and actions pan out.

38
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:28,041
Each player creates
their own character

39
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,208
and participates in the story
presented to them.

40
00:03:31,208 --> 00:03:33,416
Most of the events will be
determined by the GM,

41
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:34,833
or gamemaster.

42
00:03:34,916 --> 00:03:36,833
But depending on what
the players choose to do,

43
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:40,000
the story could take a turn
that even the GM didn't expect!

44
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,500
Are we allowed to make
a character

45
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:43,833
that's completely different
from us in real life?

46
00:03:43,916 --> 00:03:44,833
[HARUTO]
Of course.

47
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:46,166
Playing as someone different

48
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:47,458
is one of the biggest appeals

49
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:50,166
of any RPG,
but there's nothing wrong

50
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:52,083
with making your character
exactly like yourself.

51
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:54,250
Exactly like myself?

52
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:57,291
[HARUTO] The world for this game
is your typical one

53
00:03:57,375 --> 00:03:58,666
of swords and magic.

54
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,541
You're all adventurers
who have just arrived

55
00:04:00,625 --> 00:04:02,250
in a new kingdom.

56
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:05,166
With that out of the way,
let's create some characters.

57
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:06,708
I've taken the liberty
to make samples

58
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:09,333
of partially
predetermined abilities.

59
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,791
To make things easier,
we'll use them as templates.

60
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:18,416
[CHIHIRO]
Hmm.

61
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,958
[MIYAKO]
Hmm.

62
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:21,291
Hey, Fuwa?

63
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:23,208
I'm having trouble
understanding my sheet.

64
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:26,083
What does the "2D" and "3D"
next to our stats mean?

65
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:28,083
The "D" is for "dice."

66
00:04:28,166 --> 00:04:30,125
You'll make various decisions
throughout the game

67
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:31,333
by rolling your dice.

68
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:32,916
The higher
the corresponding stat is,

69
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,041
the more of them
you'll get to use.

70
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:37,208
[MIYAKO] So then "2D"
means you roll two dice,

71
00:04:37,291 --> 00:04:39,291
and "3D" means you roll three?

72
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:40,250
[HARUTO]
Exactly.

73
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,333
Silly question.

74
00:04:44,416 --> 00:04:46,458
But can we pick
whatever sex we want?

75
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:48,125
Sure can.

76
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:50,291
So does that mean you're gonna
make a female character too?

77
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:52,291
Wait, you're not going
with a guy either?

78
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:53,666
Her name is Tsukiko,

79
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,833
and she's a seventeen-year-old
female knight!

80
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:59,208
Well, if you're doing it,
I might as well do it too.

81
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:01,166
And while we're at it,
why don't I make my character

82
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,625
your character's little sister?

83
00:05:02,708 --> 00:05:03,666
Her little sister?

84
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:06,708
So you'd be
my little sister then?

85
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:09,291
I guess there's no reason
for me to say no.

86
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:11,166
Good! 'Cause I'm making
my character

87
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:12,791
your little sister, too!

88
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:14,666
She'll be the youngest
of the bunch!

89
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,416
And her hobby is doing
naughty things with Tsukiko!

90
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,125
[ITSUKI] That's not a hobby,
that's a problem!

91
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:20,750
Is that against the rules?

92
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:23,166
[HARUTO]
Uh, not exactly, but...

93
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:25,208
Yeah, whatever,
do what you want.

94
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,750
Huh?

95
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:28,791
If you three are going
to be sisters on an adventure,

96
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,625
then I guess I might
as well be one, too.

97
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:33,166
I can make my age twenty,
like I am in real life,

98
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:34,916
and that'll make me
the oldest of the bunch.

99
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,458
I like the idea of you
as an older sis.

100
00:05:37,541 --> 00:05:38,625
[laughs]

101
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:39,875
Hold on a sec.

102
00:05:39,958 --> 00:05:41,625
I'm your little sister?

103
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:43,083
[MIYAKO]
You would be, yeah.

104
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:44,958
I'm the little sister?

105
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:46,166
You're okay with that, right?

106
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:47,583
Considering your
freaky obsession?

107
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:48,583
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

108
00:05:48,666 --> 00:05:49,875
I love little sisters and all,

109
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:51,041
but that doesn't mean
I actually want

110
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:52,000
to be one myself!

111
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:53,500
That's completely different!

112
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:55,625
Then do you want me
to make my character younger?

113
00:05:57,041 --> 00:05:58,333
[grunts softly]

114
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:01,916
I guess this could work.

115
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,375
Well, what do you know?

116
00:06:03,458 --> 00:06:05,291
Five seconds of thought
and you're back on board.

117
00:06:05,375 --> 00:06:07,625
You better take
good care of me, big sis.

118
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:09,416
You're playing
the part a tad cockier

119
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,416
than necessary.

120
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,666
And let me gear up some music
for the opening.

121
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:15,833
-[phone beeps]
-There.

122
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,416
-[fanfare playing]
-Gagagia Kingdom:

123
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:20,708
a small domain that rests
on the edge of the continent.

124
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:23,666
Within its boundaries lie
many ruins and caves.

125
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,291
Countless adventurers
travel here

126
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:28,750
seeking treasure and materials
from the native monsters.

127
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:30,833
And now,
four adventuring sisters

128
00:06:30,916 --> 00:06:32,500
have arrived in the kingdom.

129
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:34,000
Will fate be kind to them?

130
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:36,208
There's only one way
to find out.

131
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:38,875
End scene.

132
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:40,375
Now, please introduce
the characters

133
00:06:40,458 --> 00:06:41,833
you've created to us all.

134
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:45,041
Okay, how about I start
since I'm the oldest?

135
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:47,291
My name is Miyako,
just spelled differently.

136
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:49,791
And I'm an expert
on attack magic.

137
00:06:49,875 --> 00:06:52,125
I also have this
one particular special attack

138
00:06:52,208 --> 00:06:54,708
where I can shoot coins
at a super high velocity.

139
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:56,625
I'm Tsukiko, the second sister.

140
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,500
I'm a female knight
with long black hair

141
00:06:58,583 --> 00:07:00,166
who fights with her sword
and shield.

142
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:03,000
My special ability
is I can reproduce any weapon,

143
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:04,625
as long as I see it once.

144
00:07:04,708 --> 00:07:06,541
[CHIHIRO]
I'm the third sister, Sen.

145
00:07:06,625 --> 00:07:08,583
I'm a thief class
who uses bows and arrows

146
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,000
as well as knives to fight.

147
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:12,333
And I have the ability
to open treasure boxes.

148
00:07:12,416 --> 00:07:15,791
I can nullify any magical attack
that touches my right hand.

149
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:18,083
Everyone is using skills
that I'm pretty sure

150
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:20,291
I've seen somewhere before,
is that okay?

151
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:22,875
It's not like our campaign
is gonna be made into a book

152
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:24,500
or an anime, so it's fine.

153
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:26,333
Well, in that case.

154
00:07:26,416 --> 00:07:27,625
Last but not least,

155
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:30,250
I'm the youngest sister,
Death Mask.

156
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:33,166
When I come in contact
with another's bodily fluids,

157
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:36,000
I can increase
their abilities tenfold.

158
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:37,708
[giggles]

159
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:40,375
Something tells me your skill
is gonna cause the most trouble.

160
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:43,708
All right,
let's start the story.

161
00:07:45,583 --> 00:07:47,333
You've all arrived
at the castle town

162
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:48,958
in Gagagia Kingdom.

163
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:50,875
It's early afternoon,
and the main street

164
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:52,916
is bustling with people.

165
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,125
Okay, team, what does
everyone want to do?

166
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,541
I say we go to the inn
and relax by exploring

167
00:07:57,625 --> 00:07:59,416
each other's private parts,
eh, Tsukiko?

168
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,708
Ten seconds in?

169
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,250
[HARUTO]
Unfortunately, you've used up

170
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,666
all of your travel money
on your way here.

171
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,416
With what you have now,
you won't be able

172
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:07,708
to sleep at any inn.

173
00:08:07,791 --> 00:08:08,875
[CHIHIRO]
Makes sense.

174
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:10,291
That just means
we'll have to find

175
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:11,666
a way to make money, right?

176
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,916
[MIYAKO] How do we
make money in this world?

177
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,083
[HARUTO]
If you go to the pub,

178
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,916
you can find some job listings.

179
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,416
Or you could go to some ruins

180
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,166
and find treasure.
Or defeat monsters.

181
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,041
Then exchange whatever
they drop for money.

182
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:24,208
You heard the man.
Let's head for the ruins.

183
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:25,625
Who knows what
we'll find in there?

184
00:08:25,708 --> 00:08:27,541
Wouldn't working be a safer bet?

185
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:30,041
You're so busy discussing
what to do next

186
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,875
that you hardly noticed
the four men

187
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:33,041
that appeared before you.

188
00:08:33,125 --> 00:08:34,916
They seem to be adventurers.

189
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,166
[chuckles]

190
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:38,333
Sounds like you ladies
are low on funds.

191
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:40,500
But we'd be happy to treat
all of you to some drinks

192
00:08:40,583 --> 00:08:41,875
and a room, what do you say?

193
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:43,916
Whoa, what? Seriously?

194
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,416
[THUG cackles]
Of course.

195
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:49,458
How lucky are we
to run into such generous guys?

196
00:08:49,541 --> 00:08:51,083
We accept your offer!

197
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:52,916
Hey! Let's think
about this, big bro--

198
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,541
I mean, big sister!

199
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:57,083
They obviously have
other intentions.

200
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:58,291
I shouldn't have
to tell you this,

201
00:08:58,375 --> 00:08:59,708
but don't go with them.

202
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:01,208
Really? Are you sure?

203
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:05,125
Oh, come on, we just wanna show
you a good time, I promise.

204
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:06,791
How dare you trick me

205
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:08,875
with the intention
of doing lewd things to us!

206
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,791
[chuckles] What?
Are you going to try

207
00:09:10,875 --> 00:09:12,458
and fight us, little girl?

208
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:14,250
[MIYAKO]
We don't have much other choice!

209
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,875
The four of us will have
to stomp you into the ground!

210
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:18,708
This might actually
be good for us.

211
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,791
If we beat them,
we can steal their money.

212
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:22,166
Color me surprised
that you're talking

213
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:24,083
about robbing
these dudes so casually.

214
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:26,208
Sen is more hardcore
than I expected.

215
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:28,375
Either way, you girls
have decided

216
00:09:28,458 --> 00:09:30,875
to fight
these shady characters.

217
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:32,500
I'll make some
battle preparations.

218
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:33,500
Give me a sec.

219
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:36,083
This is Tsukiko.

220
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,791
-This is Sen.
-[CHIHIRO] Huh.

221
00:09:37,875 --> 00:09:39,500
[HARUTO]
This is Miyako.

222
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:41,750
And this is Death Mask.

223
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:43,583
Why am I the old geezer?

224
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:45,625
All of their faces
are very stoic.

225
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:47,291
This is a western TRPG,

226
00:09:47,375 --> 00:09:49,250
so we're gonna have to work
with what we've got.

227
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:51,500
These four are your enemies.

228
00:09:51,583 --> 00:09:52,791
We'll take turns.

229
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:54,291
Order is determined by agility,

230
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,041
so highest goes first.

231
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:58,583
All right.
Let your battle begin!

232
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:06,458
[grunting]

233
00:10:06,541 --> 00:10:07,333
[THUG laughs]

234
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:08,583
What's the matter?

235
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:11,708
Aren't you going to fight back?

236
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,166
I'll rip your clothes to shreds!

237
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:19,916
Ha-ha. Wide open.

238
00:10:20,875 --> 00:10:21,750
[screams]

239
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:25,583
I've had just about enough
of you guys!

240
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:27,125
Ice Needle!

241
00:10:32,791 --> 00:10:34,625
You won't beat us that easily.

242
00:10:34,708 --> 00:10:36,041
Didn't work.

243
00:10:36,125 --> 00:10:37,791
-[THUGS laugh]
-[ITSUKI] Damn, they're strong.

244
00:10:37,875 --> 00:10:40,041
If we don't change things,
we're gonna lose.

245
00:10:40,125 --> 00:10:41,500
Myaa, you know
what we have to do!

246
00:10:41,583 --> 00:10:42,625
Are you ready?

247
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:43,958
Sorry, what?

248
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,458
I'll use my ability.

249
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:48,375
We'll power you right on up!

250
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:49,791
Then, you should be able
to defeat them

251
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:51,583
with one blast from your magic!

252
00:10:51,666 --> 00:10:53,333
You can't fool me!
I know your ability

253
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:55,083
requires us
to do pervy fan service.

254
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:56,791
-No, thanks!
-[NAYUTA] Don't worry.

255
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,708
We just have to share
