They're so fun!

512
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,166
[CHIHIRO] Yeah. I'd like
to play one again.

513
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,500
I'm really glad
you had a good time!

514
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:52,791
It wasn't bad, but I didn't
get to power up

515
00:20:52,875 --> 00:20:54,625
Itsuki's character even once.

516
00:20:54,708 --> 00:20:56,375
I'll have
to try harder next time.

517
00:20:56,458 --> 00:20:58,125
I would prefer it if you didn't.

518
00:20:58,208 --> 00:20:59,875
[chuckles]
All right, well.

519
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,875
I'll start thinking
about our next campaign, then.

520
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:03,375
Looking forward to it.

521
00:21:03,458 --> 00:21:04,625
And you need to start thinking

522
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:06,208
about learning
some self-respect.

523
00:21:06,291 --> 00:21:07,708
[NAYUTA]
Oh, come on.

524
00:21:07,791 --> 00:21:09,625
I didn't hear your character
complaining about it,

525
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:11,500
Miss One-Woman-Army.

526
00:21:14,875 --> 00:21:16,875
-Thanks for this, Itsuki.
-Hmm?

527
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:18,083
What do you mean?

528
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:20,291
The game we played today,

529
00:21:20,375 --> 00:21:22,250
it was all to cheer me up,
wasn't it?

530
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:24,583
Mmm. D-Don't get
the wrong idea, man!

531
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:27,833
I just had a sudden urge
to try a tabletop RPG!

532
00:21:27,916 --> 00:21:29,791
-Yeah, that figures.
-[scoffs]

533
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:32,833
You know...

534
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:36,875
it's a lot of fun
to create something.

535
00:21:36,958 --> 00:21:40,166
And it makes me happy when
people enjoy what I've made.

536
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:42,125
No matter how much
or how little.

537
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,583
I bet it's the same for them.

538
00:21:45,666 --> 00:21:47,041
My anime team.

539
00:21:47,125 --> 00:21:50,208
Sure, there some
rough times along the way.

540
00:21:50,291 --> 00:21:51,875
And in the end,
it didn't pan out.

541
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:55,291
But the fact that we all
worked hard on this thing

542
00:21:55,375 --> 00:21:56,291
wasn't a waste.

543
00:21:57,375 --> 00:21:58,458
At least, I think.

544
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:03,541
So there's no reason
I should stop giving

545
00:22:03,625 --> 00:22:05,250
a hundred percent now, right?

546
00:22:08,583 --> 00:22:09,875
No, man.

547
00:22:11,208 --> 00:22:12,166
Yeah.

548
00:23:29,916 --> 00:23:32,000
-Hey, Itsuki?
-Huh?

549
00:23:33,083 --> 00:23:35,125
Does Miyako have...

550
00:23:35,208 --> 00:23:36,708
a boyfriend

551
00:23:36,791 --> 00:23:37,750
or what?

552
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:41,958
Huh?

